snippet.title: Kambua – Siendi Bila Wewe (Official Music Video) SKIZA 95211786
snippet.description:
“Siendi Bila Wewe” is a deeply moving worship song written and produced by J Blessing, brought to life through a powerful performance by Kambua.

The song is a heartfelt cry of dependence on God’s presence, echoing the words of Exodus 33:15: “If Your Presence does not go with us, do not send us up from here.”

Filmed at the historic Kikuyu Church (built in 1909), the song blends heartfelt vocals with a strong choir to create an atmosphere of surrender and victory in Christ.

🙏 Stream & Share to spread the message of God’s presence.

📖 Lyrics (Swahili & English Translation)

[Intro]
Siendi peke yangu… (I won’t go alone)
Siendi bila Wewe… (I won’t go without You)
Uwepo wako, Baba… (Your presence, Father)
Ndio ushindi wangu… (That’s my victory)

[Chorus]
Siendi peke yangu (I won’t go alone)
Siendi bila Wewe (I won’t go without You)
Uwepo wako, Baba (Your presence, Father)
Ndio ushindi wangu (That’s my victory)

[Verse 1]
Nina ndoto, nina safari (I have dreams, I have a journey)
Lakini zote ni bure bila Wewe (But all is nothing without You)
Hatua moja bila upako (One step without anointing)
Ni kama giza lisilo na nuru (Is like darkness without light)

[Chorus ]
(Repeat in Swahili & English as above)

[Verse 2 ]
Kama Musa alivyosema (As Moses said)
Bila Wewe hatutasonga (Without You we cannot move forward)
Wewe ndiye unayetutofautisha (You are the One who sets us apart)
Wewe ndiye pumzi ya maisha (You are the breath of life)

[Bridge ]
Niongoze… (Niongoze) (Lead me… Lead me)
Nishike… (Nishike) (Hold me… Hold me)
Usiende mbali… (Usiende mbali) (Don’t go far… Don’t go far)
Baba yangu… (Baba yangu) (My Father… My Father)

[Chorus]
Siendi peke yangu (I won’t go alone)
Siendi bila Wewe (I won’t go without You)
Uwepo wako, Baba (Your presence, Father)
Ndio ushindi wangu (That’s my victory)

[Outro]
Siendi peke yangu… (I won’t go alone)
Siendi bila Wewe… (I won’t go without You)
Baba… Baba… (Father… Father…)
Ndio ushindi wangu… (That’s my victory…)

⸻

🎶 Credits
 • Artist: Kambua
 • Songwriter & Producer: J Blessing
 • Audio Engineer: Saint p
 • Mixing & Mastering: Sofresh 
 • Choir Vocals: Sheila Wa Tele, Timothy Kaluva , Nyambura Gichamba , Steve Homes , Liz Homes, Vivian Kimemia, Wanja Gacuvi 
 • Video Director: J Blessing
 • Shot on Location: Watson-Scott Memorial Church, Thogoto (1909)

snippet.title: Otile Brown ft Nviiri - Furaha yako (Official Video)
snippet.description:
Otile Brown teams up with Nviiri the Storyteller for “Furaha,” a soulful Afro-R&B ballad about love, patience, and devotion. Blending heartfelt Swahili lyricism with smooth melodies, the song paints the story of a man ready to give his all — love, peace, and furaha — to the woman he adores, even when she overlooks him.
With Otile’s signature vocals and Nviiri’s storytelling touch, “Furaha” captures the universal struggle of waiting for love to be recognized, balancing pain with hope. It’s a powerful anthem of vulnerability, persistence, and the beauty of knowing your worth.
